						<summary>

						<p>Hero-stone (No. 7) set up in a field to the west of the village.</p>						

						<p>Circa 10th century.</p>						

						<p>This record registers a gift of land under the tank called the Baḍaṅgāni-keṟe, by the king and the <hi rend="italic">ūru</hi> of Maṅgala in memory of a hero whose name is not clear, who died during a cattle-raid. It states that Vajradēva was ruling over Puli-nāḍu.</p>						

						</summary>
